# ‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ēó‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ēĎ‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ēĎ  ‚Ėą‚Ėą‚ēĎ
# ‚ēö‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēĚ‚ēö‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēź‚ēĚ‚ēö‚ēź‚ēĚ  ‚ēö‚ēź‚ēĚ
# Z Shell - powerful command interpreter.
#

#!/usr/bin/env zsh

if [[ -n "$ZSH_DEBUG" ]]; then
  zmodload zsh/zprof
fi

# Emacs
bindkey -e

# In WSL, ensure we use Linux paths for mise, not Windows paths
if [[ -n "$WSL_DISTRO_NAME" ]] || grep -qiE "(microsoft|wsl)" /proc/version 2>/dev/null; then
  export MISE_DATA_DIR="$HOME/.local/share/mise"
  export MISE_CONFIG_DIR="$HOME/.config/mise"
  export MISE_CACHE_DIR="$HOME/.cache/mise"
  export MISE_STATE_DIR="$HOME/.local/state/mise"
  # CRITICAL: early-init settings must be env vars, NOT mise.toml
  export MISE_IGNORED_CONFIG_PATHS="/mnt/c:/mnt/d"
  export MISE_CEILING_PATHS="/mnt"
  [[ "$PWD" == /mnt/* ]] && cd "$HOME"
fi


if [[ -n "$ENV_DIRS" ]]; then
  for dir in ${(s/:/)ENV_DIRS}; do
    [[ ! -d "$dir" ]] && mkdir -p "$dir"
  done
  unset ENV_DIRS
fi

# ZSH Syntax Theme (rendered from .chezmoidata/theme.yaml ‚Üí .theme.name)
[[ -r "$ZDOTDIR/colors/{{ .theme.name }}.zsh-syntax-theme" ]] && source "$ZDOTDIR/colors/{{ .theme.name }}.zsh-syntax-theme"

# Lazy-load (autoload) Zsh function files from a directory.
export ZFUNCDIR="$ZDOTDIR/.zfunctions"

# Set zshrc.d directory for mattmc3/zshrc.d plugin
export ZSHRCD="$ZDOTDIR/.zshrc.d"

# Set any zstyles
[[ -r "$ZDOTDIR/.zstyles" ]] && source "$ZDOTDIR/.zstyles"

{{- $remote_tier := (index . "remote_tier" | default "full") }}
{{- $homelab_zsh := or (eq $remote_tier "minimal") (eq $remote_tier "medium") (index . "is_raspi" | default false) }}
{{- if $homelab_zsh }}
# Homelab/remote tier: keep startup small and deterministic.
# This intentionally bypasses antidote and sources only curated local fragments.
export ZSH_HOMELAB_MINIMAL=1

_source_zshrcd() {
  local _file="$ZSHRCD/$1"
  [[ -r "$_file" ]] && source "$_file"
}

_source_zshrcd 00-helpers.zsh
_source_zshrcd 01-mise.zsh
_source_zshrcd 10-dirs.zsh
_source_zshrcd 20-paths.zsh
_source_zshrcd 25-homelab-aliases.zsh
_source_zshrcd 25-homelab-functions.zsh
_source_zshrcd 25-history.zsh
_source_zshrcd 30-misc.zsh
_source_zshrcd 50-mise.zsh

if [[ -n "$ENV_DIRS" ]]; then
  for dir in ${(s/:/)ENV_DIRS}; do
    [[ ! -d "$dir" ]] && mkdir -p "$dir"
  done
  unset ENV_DIRS
fi

autoload -Uz compinit
compinit -d "${ZSH_COMPDUMP:-${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-$HOME/.cache}/zsh/zcompdump-${ZSH_VERSION}}" -C

(( $+commands[fzf] )) && _source_zshrcd 80-fzf.zsh
(( $+commands[eza] )) && _source_zshrcd 80-eza.zsh
(( $+commands[zoxide] )) && _source_zshrcd 80-zoxide.zsh
(( $+commands[bat] )) && _source_zshrcd 80-bat.zsh
(( $+commands[rg] )) && _source_zshrcd 80-ripgrep.zsh

if (( $+commands[starship] )); then
  _source_zshrcd 90-starship.zsh
else
  PROMPT='%F{green}%n@%m%f:%F{blue}%~%f %# '
fi
_source_zshrcd 80-homelab-plugins.zsh

unset -f _source_zshrcd
{{- else }}
# Clone antidote if necessary.
export ANTIDOTE_HOME="${XDG_DATA_HOME:-$HOME/.local/share}/antidote"

if [[ ! -d "$ANTIDOTE_HOME" ]]; then
  git clone https://github.com/mattmc3/antidote "$ANTIDOTE_HOME"
fi

source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/antidote.zsh"
antidote load

# for _rc in $ZDOTDIR/.zshrc.d/*.zsh; do
#   # Ignore tilde files.
#   if [[ $_rc:t != '~'* ]]; then
#     source "$_rc"
#     echo "$_rc"
#   fi
# done
# unset _rc

# ========================= Visual Settings ====================================

# LS_COLORS is set by vivid in 80-eza.zsh using the active theme from chezmoi
# Legacy dircolors fallback only if vivid is not installed
if ! command -v vivid >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  if command -v dircolors >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    eval "$(dircolors --sh)"
  elif command -v gdircolors >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    eval "$(gdircolors --sh)"
  fi
fi
{{- end }}

if [[ -n "$ZSH_DEBUG" ]]; then
  zprof
fi

